---
// Chert Technology Page - Deep dive into the technology
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Technology — CHERT" description="Deep dive into Chert's layered architecture: Alluvium, Tephra, Crystallite, Lithification, and Cali.">
  
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="relative min-h-[60vh] flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden pt-24">
    <!-- Background -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-void">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-pattern opacity-20"></div>
      <div class="absolute top-1/3 left-1/4 w-[600px] h-[600px] rounded-full bg-silica/10 blur-[150px]"></div>
      <div class="absolute bottom-1/4 right-1/4 w-[400px] h-[400px] rounded-full bg-quantum/10 blur-[120px]"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative z-10 max-w-[1600px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 py-20 text-center">
      <span class="text-quantum font-display text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">Technology</span>
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-bold text-snow mt-4 mb-6">
        Built for
        <span class="gradient-text">Impossibility</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-xl text-silver leading-relaxed">
        Five branded layers. Post-quantum cryptography. Meaningful computation.
        Every component engineered for the future.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Consensus Deep Dive -->
  <section class="py-32 bg-obsidian relative overflow-hidden" id="consensus">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 grid-pattern opacity-10"></div>
    
    <div class="relative max-w-[1600px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <!-- Section Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-20">
        <span class="text-silica-bright font-display text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">Consensus Architecture</span>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-snow mt-4 mb-6">
          Alluvium + Tephra + Crystallite + Lithification + Cali
        </h2>
        <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-silver text-lg">
          When you hit send, you should see your transaction immediately, watch it apply to your account, and know exactly when it becomes permanent.
          Chert’s pipeline delivers a fast, consistent <span class="text-snow">pending</span> state and then locks it in with <span class="text-snow">aBFT finality</span>—typically in under a second.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 1: Alluvium -->
      <div class="mb-24">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-silica to-silica-glow flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="font-display font-bold text-snow text-lg">1</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-snow">Alluvium</h3>
                <p class="text-silica-bright text-sm font-mono">DATA PLANE</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-silver leading-relaxed mb-6">
               Your transactions are collected into micro-batches and rapidly propagated across the network.
               Alluvium is the Narwhal-inspired data plane focused on <span class="text-snow">getting your data everywhere fast</span> so the next layers can order, apply, and checkpoint it without slowing you down.
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Micro-Batching</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Your transaction is grouped into a batch and broadcast immediately, so you can see it as <span class="text-snow">pending</span> quickly.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">DAG Structure</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Batches form a DAG so the network can move many transactions at once without a single bottleneck.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Erasure Coding</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Your batch stays retrievable even if some validators go offline or act maliciously.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Visual -->
          <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8">
            <div class="aspect-square relative">
              <!-- DAG Visualization -->
              <svg viewBox="0 0 300 300" class="w-full h-full">
                <!-- Nodes -->
                <circle cx="150" cy="50" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.9"/>
                <circle cx="80" cy="120" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.8"/>
                <circle cx="220" cy="120" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.8"/>
                <circle cx="50" cy="200" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="150" cy="200" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="250" cy="200" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.7"/>
                <circle cx="100" cy="270" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.6"/>
                <circle cx="200" cy="270" r="20" fill="url(#silicaGradient)" opacity="0.6"/>
                
                <!-- Edges -->
                <line x1="150" y1="70" x2="80" y2="100" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="150" y1="70" x2="220" y2="100" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="80" y1="140" x2="50" y2="180" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="80" y1="140" x2="150" y2="180" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="220" y1="140" x2="150" y2="180" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="220" y1="140" x2="250" y2="180" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="50" y1="220" x2="100" y2="250" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="150" y1="220" x2="100" y2="250" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="150" y1="220" x2="200" y2="250" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                <line x1="250" y1="220" x2="200" y2="250" stroke="#60a5fa" stroke-width="2" opacity="0.5"/>
                
                <!-- Gradient -->
                <defs>
                  <linearGradient id="silicaGradient" x1="0%" y1="0%" x2="100%" y2="100%">
                    <stop offset="0%" style="stop-color:#3b82f6"/>
                    <stop offset="100%" style="stop-color:#2563eb"/>
                  </linearGradient>
                </defs>
              </svg>
              <div class="absolute bottom-4 left-4 right-4 text-center">
                <p class="text-silver text-sm">Directed Acyclic Graph Structure</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 2: Tephra -->
       <div class="mb-16">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <!-- Visual -->
          <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8 order-2 lg:order-1">
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V1</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V2</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V3</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V4</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/40 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border-2 border-quantum">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm font-bold">PROP</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V6</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V7</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V8</span>
                </div>
                <div class="aspect-square bg-quantum/20 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center border border-quantum/30">
                  <span class="text-quantum font-mono text-sm">V9</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-silver text-sm">Deterministic Commit Linearization</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="order-1 lg:order-2">
            <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-quantum to-quantum-glow flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="font-display font-bold text-void text-lg">2</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-snow">Tephra</h3>
                <p class="text-quantum text-sm font-mono">ORDERING LAYER</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-silver leading-relaxed mb-6">
               Tephra turns network-wide batches into a single, shared history.
               It <span class="text-snow">sorts and commits batches to the DAG</span> quickly (often <span class="text-snow">&lt; 300ms</span>), which is what enables near-instant <span class="text-snow">pending</span> transactions.
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
               <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Instant Pending</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Once your batch is committed into the DAG, wallets can reliably show your transfer as <span class="text-snow">pending</span> without waiting for “confirmations”.</p>
               </div>
               <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Verifiable Ordering</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Compact certificate proofs let any node verify the ordering of your batch without expensive re-checking.</p>
               </div>
               <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Stays Responsive</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Timeout and recovery rules keep your pending experience smooth—even during congestion or partitions.</p>
               </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
       </div>

      <!-- Layer 3: Crystallite -->
       <div class="mb-24">
         <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8 lg:p-10">
           <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-10 items-center">
             <div class="lg:col-span-1">
               <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-3 mb-4">
                 <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-snow/80 to-silver/40 flex items-center justify-center">
                   <span class="font-display font-bold text-void text-lg">+</span>
                 </div>
                 <div>
                   <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-snow">Crystallite</h3>
                   <p class="text-silver text-sm font-mono">EXECUTION / APPLY</p>
                 </div>
               </div>

               <p class="text-silver leading-relaxed">
                 After your transaction is ordered, it flows through Crystallite—Chert’s deterministic execution/apply layer—so results apply cleanly to your account.
                 This is what turns “pending” into visible balance and state updates for transfers <span class="text-snow">in and out</span> of your wallet.
               </p>
             </div>

             <div class="lg:col-span-2">
               <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                 <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                   <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Parallel Lanes</h4>
                   <p class="text-silver text-sm">Independent lanes execute safely in parallel for speed.</p>
                 </div>
                 <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                   <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Deterministic Results</h4>
                   <p class="text-silver text-sm">Same inputs always produce the same outputs across every validator.</p>
                 </div>
                 <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                   <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Account Updates</h4>
                   <p class="text-silver text-sm">State changes are applied and indexed so your wallet reflects them quickly.</p>
                 </div>
               </div>
             </div>
           </div>
         </div>
       </div>

        <!-- Layer 4: Lithification -->
      <div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-3 mb-6">
              <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-nebula to-nebula-bright flex items-center justify-center">
                <span class="font-display font-bold text-snow text-lg">3</span>
              </div>
              <div>
                 <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-snow">Lithification</h3>
                <p class="text-nebula-bright text-sm font-mono">PROOFS / CHECKPOINTS</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-silver leading-relaxed mb-6">
               Lithification packages the finalized result into anchors, certificates, and sync-friendly checkpoints.
               Once Crystallite has applied Tephra order, Lithification turns the result into portable proof surfaces: <span class="text-snow">auditable, replayable, and permanent</span>.
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-4">
               <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Proof Packaging</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Anchors and certificates package finalized state into proof surfaces for wallets, explorers, and recovery.</p>
               </div>
               <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Checkpoint Boundaries</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Lineations and related checkpoints make replay, pruning, and fast sync safer and simpler.</p>
               </div>
               <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                 <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Post-Quantum Proofs</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver text-sm">Finality certificates are backed by post-quantum signatures designed to stay safe as computing changes.</p>
               </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Visual -->
          <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8">
            <div class="text-center">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-6 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-br from-nebula to-nebula-bright flex items-center justify-center">
                <svg class="w-16 h-16 text-snow" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"></path>
                </svg>
              </div>
               <h4 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-snow mb-2">From Pending to Permanent</h4>
                 <p class="text-silver">Typically ~0.5s to show as pending, with ordered, applied, and checkpointed transfers finalized in under 1s.</p>
               <div class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-white/10">
                 <div class="text-4xl font-display font-bold text-nebula-bright">&lt; 1s</div>
                 <div class="text-silver text-sm">Typical end-to-end finality</div>
               </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 5: Cali -->
      <div class="mt-24">
        <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8 lg:p-10">
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-10 items-center">
            <div class="lg:col-span-1">
              <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-3 mb-4">
                <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-amber-400 to-amber-500 flex items-center justify-center">
                  <span class="font-display font-bold text-void text-lg">5</span>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-snow">Cali</h3>
                  <p class="text-amber-300 text-sm font-mono">MONITORING / RECOVERY</p>
                </div>
              </div>

              <p class="text-silver leading-relaxed">
                Cali is the watchdog around the stack. It tracks health, observes finalized checkpoints, and helps the network recover cleanly when liveness degrades.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="lg:col-span-2">
              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
                <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Health Signals</h4>
                  <p class="text-silver text-sm">Peer readiness, liveness, and progress tracking across the stack.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Recovery Hooks</h4>
                  <p class="text-silver text-sm">Restart and catch-up flows use checkpoints to restore clean progress.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="glass-light rounded-lg p-4">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-semibold text-snow mb-2">Operational Safety</h4>
                  <p class="text-silver text-sm">The network stays observable and recoverable under churn, latency, or partial partitions.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Post-Quantum Security -->
  <section class="py-32 bg-void relative overflow-hidden" id="security">
    <div class="absolute top-1/3 right-1/4 w-[500px] h-[500px] bg-nebula/10 blur-[150px]"></div>
    
    <div class="relative max-w-[1600px] mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
      <div class="text-center mb-20">
        <span class="text-nebula-bright font-display text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase">Security</span>
        <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-snow mt-4 mb-6">
          Post-Quantum Cryptography
        </h2>
        <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-silver text-lg">
          Built for a world where quantum computers exist. NIST-approved algorithms protect your assets today and tomorrow.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
        <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8 hover:border-nebula/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-nebula to-nebula-bright flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-snow" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15.232 5.232l3.536 3.536m-2.036-5.036a2.5 2.5 0 113.536 3.536L6.5 21.036H3v-3.572L16.732 3.732z"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-snow mb-3">Dilithium-2</h3>
          <p class="text-silver text-sm leading-relaxed">
            NIST-selected lattice-based digital signature scheme. Resistant to Shor's algorithm attacks on elliptic curves.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8 hover:border-nebula/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-nebula to-nebula-bright flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-snow" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7h12m0 0l-4-4m4 4l-4 4m0 6H4m0 0l4 4m-4-4l4-4"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-snow mb-3">Hybrid Approach</h3>
          <p class="text-silver text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Classical (Ed25519) and post-quantum signatures combined. Defense in depth against unknown vulnerabilities.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass rounded-2xl p-8 hover:border-nebula/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="w-14 h-14 rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-nebula to-nebula-bright flex items-center justify-center mb-6">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7 text-snow" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15"></path>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-bold text-snow mb-3">Upgradeable</h3>
          <p class="text-silver text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Cryptographic agility built-in. Upgrade algorithms without hard forks as standards evolve.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="py-32 bg-obsidian relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0">
      <div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-[800px] h-[400px] bg-gradient-to-r from-quantum/10 via-silica/10 to-nebula/10 blur-[150px] rounded-full"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-snow mb-6">
        Ready to Build?
      </h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-silver leading-relaxed mb-12">
        Explore our documentation, SDKs, and developer resources.
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="https://silica.network/developers" class="btn-quantum btn-premium">
          Developer Docs
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/Silica-Protocol" class="btn-ghost btn-premium">
          View Source
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .glass-light {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
  }

  .glass {
    background: rgba(26, 26, 36, 0.6);
    backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
  }

  .grid-pattern {
    background-image: 
      linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.02) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.02) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 60px 60px;
  }

  .gradient-text {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #fbbf24, #f59e0b, #3b82f6, #8b5cf6, #fbbf24);
    background-size: 400% 400%;
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    animation: gradientShift 8s ease infinite;
  }

  @keyframes gradientShift {
    0%, 100% { background-position: 0% 50%; }
    50% { background-position: 100% 50%; }
  }

  .btn-premium {
    position: relative;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 1rem 2.5rem;
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 600;
